HEADWORD: Evagination
<hw>E*vag`i*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>evaginatio</ets> an extending, <ets>evaginare</ets> to unsheathe;
<ets>e</ets> out + <ets>vagina</ets> sheath.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of unsheathing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An outgrowth or protruded part.</def>⟦br⟧
